Telecommunications group MTN has appointed Dirk Karl to head up group procurement and supply chain management, effective November 1. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; He will be responsible for developing and executing global procurement and sourcing strategies, as well as leveraging MTN&rsquo;s scale to identify opportunities to drive greater commercial success across the group&rsquo;s footprint.&nbsp; &nbsp; &ldquo;I am excited to join a company of MTN&rsquo;s scale and stature and, more so, to be given the opportunity to be part of the team that will contribute to the organisation&rsquo;s future success,&rdquo; he said. Karl has held many senior management roles in various global corporates, including General Motors, ING Group and T-Systems, in a career spanning more than two decades.&nbsp;